cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.DS, cs.CYBER, cs.DB 

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category as it focuses on analyzing the dynamics of a social network. It could also belong to cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) as it uses computational methods to study social phenomena. Additionally, it involves data analysis and modeling, which could place it in the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DB (Databases) sub-categories. Finally, as the paper deals with online social networks, it could also be classified under cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy).
